MURAL CONTEST AND PRIZE

Columbia University's Center for the Study of Ethnicity and Race invites
concepts for a mural to be placed at the Center and unveiled on April =
21,
2006.  The occasion is the commemoration of the tenth anniversary of the
student strike for ethnic studies that helped establish the Center for =
the
Study of Ethnicity and Race.  The mural should be approximately 3 by 9 =
feet,
and should depict not only the 1996 student strike but also the =
struggles of
racialized minority peoples in education broadly for ethnic studies and =
the
democratization of U.S. higher education.  A selection jury will select =
the
winning entry, which will be awarded a $500 prize.  Deadline for =
concepts
(sketches and descriptions):  January 15, 2006.  Send to Gary Y. =
Okihiro,
Center for the Study of Ethnicity and Race, 420 Hamilton Hall, 1130
Amsterdam Avenue, Columbia University, New York, NY 10027, or =
electronically
to gyo3@columbia.edu.  For more information, call 212-854-0508.  =20


